# Clerk Authentication & Data Isolation

All authentication is handled by **Clerk**. Every data access must be scoped to the authenticated user — users must never be able to read or modify data belonging to another user.

## Protected Pages & Unauthenticated Access

This app has **no dedicated sign-in page**. Sign-in and sign-up are triggered via modal buttons on the homepage (`/`).

When a user tries to access a protected page without being authenticated, **redirect them to the homepage** (`/`) — never to a `/sign-in` route.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — redirect unauthenticated users to the homepage
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) redirect("/");
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — redirecting to a sign-in page that does not exist
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) redirect("/sign-in"); // ❌ this page does not exist
```

Also ensure `clerkMiddleware` in `middleware.ts` does **not** set `signInUrl` to a `/sign-in` route. Leave it unset or point it to `/`.

## Getting the Current User

Always use Clerk's server-side helpers to get the authenticated user ID. Never trust user-supplied IDs from request bodies or query params as the identity source.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — server action / route handler
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthenticated");

// Use userId to scope all DB queries
const decks = await db.query.decks.findMany({
  where: eq(decks.userId, userId),
});
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — never trust client-supplied userId
const { userId } = req.body; // attacker can forge this
const decks = await db.query.decks.findMany({
  where: eq(decks.userId, userId),
});
```

## Mutating Data (update / delete)

Always verify ownership before mutating. Fetch the record and confirm `record.userId === userId` before proceeding.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const { userId } = await auth();
const deck = await db.query.decks.findFirst({ where: eq(decks.id, deckId) });

if (!deck || deck.userId !== userId) {
  throw new Error("Forbidden");
}

await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));
```

## Rules

- Always call `auth()` (server) or `useAuth()` (client) from `@clerk/nextjs` — never roll your own session logic.
- Unauthenticated users accessing protected pages must be redirected to `/` (the homepage), never to `/sign-in`.
- Every DB query that returns user-specific data **must** include a `userId` filter.
- Every mutation (insert, update, delete) **must** verify the record belongs to the current user before executing.
- Return generic `"Forbidden"` / `404` errors — never leak whether a resource exists to an unauthorized user.
- Protect all API routes and server actions; never assume a route is safe because it's "internal".
